The paper discusses a communication system architecture that achieves high spectral efficiency through the use of Time-Division Duplexing (TDD) and Massive MIMO techniques. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel Network-MIMO TDD architecture, which involves cooperation between multiple base stations, and optimization of the system for different user equivalence classes. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) or Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the use of uplink pilot signals and frequency reuse across cells, which suggests that it may also belong to the Computer Communications (cs.COM) sub-category.
